Note:  This software is a direct descendant of the E.J. Rupp version.
Other versions may exist.

Changes from the original for the Amiga version:

          - nested include files
          - nested conditional assembly
          - redefinable symbols
          - segment (CODE, DATA etc.) statements
          - new manual with examples
          - ';' acceptable for comments
          - ';' comments acceptable any where in line fixing comment after
                label bug
          - '=' is now equivalent for EQU
          - automatic paging of listing
          - Amiga accepts source code from MS-DOS
          - continuous include file line numbering option
          - MS-DOS (CR,LF EOL) compatible S record output for Amiga

These cross assemblers run from the CLI only.
